title: Response cache puts full envelope on process argv (ARG_MAX + process-list leak)
updated_at: "2026-07-15T06:42:33Z"
---
## Problem
`cacheResponse` passes the full JSON envelope as a shell-quoted argv to `cache-response.sh` via Plasma `executable` DataSource. Large error HTML (truncated only after 200k) or multi-profile bursts can hit ARG_MAX; response bodies can briefly appear in `ps` listings.

## Location
`contents/ui/ProfileController.qml` (`cacheResponse` / `enqueueCacheWrite`)
`contents/scripts/cache-response.sh` (`$3` payload)

## Suggested fix
Write payload via a temp file or stdin (e.g. script reads from a path arg, or base64 file under `/tmp` created by a short write helper), not command-line argv. Keep truncation as a backstop.

## Source
Post-merge test of feat/response-cache (PIRFL residual major)